text: Missoula County is a county found in the State of Montana. As of the 2020 United States Census, the population was 117,922, making it Montana's third- most populous county. Its county seat and largest city is Missoula. It was created in 1860. == References == Category:1860s establishments in Montana Territory Category:1860 establishments in the United States Category:Montana counties
